  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dd9\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dd9\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A special statement from the President about Corona",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe made a special statement today (02) and requested the people to resort to vaccination as soon as possible as the risk of Covid is rising again.",
        "The Ministry of Health has issued health guidelines paying special attention to this and Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe, who requested the people to follow the instructions properly, emphasized that the spread of the Covid epidemic in the country should not be allowed again.",
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe made a special statement regarding the Covid and Monkey Fox epidemic and said:",
        "\u201cThe number of Covid-19 cases and deaths is increasing again. 1731 Covid patients were reported in April. There were 26 Covid deaths. That situation decreased to 472 patients in May. 13 deaths were reported. The number of Covid patients in June is 283. 3 deaths. But in July, the number of Covid patients has increased to 1616. 35 deaths. 28 of these 35 deaths occurred after July 18. Looking at this, one more thing is visible. That is that the Covid vaccine should be given immediately.",
        "17 million were vaccinated in the first round. In the second round, it was reduced to 14 million. In the third round, 8 million people have received the Covid vaccine. Only 22,623 people have been vaccinated in the 4th round. The number of vaccinations for the third and fourth times has decreased, especially in the Western Province. Therefore, people should be re-directed for vaccination.",
        "There are currently 8 million vaccines in Sri Lanka. It can be used till October. Those 8 million vaccines cannot be finished in October. Therefore, a part has to be given to another country. The vaccine was brought for you. Therefore, I request all those who have not received the vaccine to get the vaccine as soon as possible.",
        "The Ministry of Health gives advice on this. Everyone should act according to that advice. In addition, the Ministry of Health has focused on the \"Monkey Fox\" epidemic. Currently it has not arrived in Sri Lanka. The first step has been taken to prevent the disease from coming to Sri Lanka.",
        "Plans are being made to provide treatment if needed. At this time think about health and act. I request all parties not to give another chance to the covid epidemic in this country\"."
      ],
